#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:1
msgid "Panoramica"
msgstr "Overview"

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:3
msgid "Scopo"
msgstr "Purpose"

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:5
msgid ""
"Restituire la deviazione standard come radice quadrata della varianza calcolata da "
"[`variance`](../variance.md)."
msgstr ""
"Return the standard deviation as the square root of the variance computed by "
"[`variance`](../variance.md)."

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:7
msgid "Parametri"
msgstr "Parameters"

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:9
msgid "`x`: dati numerici."
msgstr "`x`: numeric data."

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:10
msgid "`w`: pesi opzionali."
msgstr "`w`: optional weights."

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:11
msgid "`ddof`: correzione sui gradi di liberta passata direttamente a `variance`."
msgstr "`ddof`: degrees-of-freedom correction passed directly to `variance`."

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:13
msgid "Restituisce"
msgstr "Returns"

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:15
msgid "Un `float` con la deviazione standard."
msgstr "A `float` with the standard deviation."

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:17
msgid "Errori ed eccezioni"
msgstr "Errors and exceptions"

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:19
msgid ""
"Eredita gli stessi errori di [`variance`](../variance.md), perche la funzione e un semplice "
"wrapper sopra quel calcolo."
msgstr ""
"It inherits the same errors as [`variance`](../variance.md), because the function is a simple "
"wrapper around that computation."

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:21
msgid "Esempio"
msgstr "Example"

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:30
msgid "Note"
msgstr "Notes"

#: ../../source/moduli/stats_utils/standard-deviation/panoramica.md:32
msgid ""
"Se vuoi capire in dettaglio il controllo su pesi e denominatore, la pagina rilevante e quella di "
"[`variance`](../variance.md)."
msgstr ""
"If you want to understand the weight and denominator checks in detail, the relevant page is "
"[`variance`](../variance.md)."

